# Premium Corporate Pitch Deck Web App

This plan details the implementation of a modern, premium web-based pitch deck prototype for an offshore software development company. The visual style will be a hybrid of Stripe, Vercel, and Accenture—focusing on a dark luxury theme, minimal futuristic enterprise aesthetics, and technical sophistication.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The target platform is an HTML/JS/CSS based web application that functions as an interactive presentation/pitch deck. Is it okay to build this as a standalone index.html/style.css project within the current directory, or do you prefer using a framework like Vite/Next.js? For maximum flexibility and as requested by the system prompts, I will use Vanilla CSS and a standard web setup unless you specify otherwise.

> [!NOTE]
> I will generate abstract network visuals, cloud infrastructure illustrations, and other graphics using my image generation tool. Since these will be AI-generated, they will follow the "subtle gradient glows" and "dark luxury" theme.

## Proposed Changes

We will create a multi-slide single-page web app (or a vertical scroll presentation) with reusable slide layouts.

### Structure & Setup

#### [NEW] [index.html](file:///c:/Users/Shaker/OneDrive/Desktop/APTITI%20PITCH%20DECk/index.html)
The main structure of the pitch deck containing the semantic HTML for all slide components. It will use a slider or vertical scrolling mechanism to transition between sections.

#### [NEW] [style.css](file:///c:/Users/Shaker/OneDrive/Desktop/APTITI%20PITCH%20DECk/style.css)
The core design system containing:
- CSS variables for deep navy/black backgrounds, electric blue accents, and white typography.
- Utility classes for grid-based layouts, spacing (generous margins, high padding), and typography scales.
- Glassmorphism effects and subtle gradient glow utilities.
- Specific styles for each slide layout (Title, Service Showcase, Case Study, etc.).

#### [NEW] [app.js](file:///c:/Users/Shaker/OneDrive/Desktop/APTITI%20PITCH%20DECk/app.js)
Logic for slide transitions, micro-animations, and interactive elements.

### Slide Layouts to Implement (in `index.html`)

1. **Title Slide**: Clean, large bold typography (geometric sans-serif), electric blue accent glow, abstract network background.
2. **Trust Metrics**: 3-card metric layout (referencing AI Metrics competitor) emphasizing large numbers and scale credibility.
3. **Service Showcase**: Grid layout detailing technical services (e.g., Team Augmentation, Custom Software) using elegant modern technical iconography.
4. **Technology Stack Visuals**: A visual representation of the tech stack using glowing icons or system architecture inspired patterns.
5. **Process Timeline**: A linear or wavy path (referencing Normastroy competitor) showing the engineering workflow.
6. **Case Study**: Split-screen layout (referencing Greener competitor) with technical metrics and data flow visuals.
7. **Comparison Table**: Clean enterprise comparison against traditional models, using glassmorphism for rows and sharp section dividers.
8. **CTA Closing Slide**: Minimalist contact and next steps slide aimed at enterprise decision-makers.

### Generated Graphics

I will use my image generation capabilities to create custom background patterns and technical illustrations tailored to the dark luxury theme.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- No automated testing suite required for this visual prototype.

### Manual Verification
- Visual inspection of the HTML file in a local browser to ensure responsiveness, color accuracy, and premium aesthetic alignment.
- Interaction check to verify slide transitions and micro-animations feel smooth and "Vercel-like".
